#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/zfs/_index.adoc:497
msgid ""
"Creating a ZFS storage pool (_zpool_) involves making a number of decisions "
"that are relatively permanent because the structure of the pool cannot be "
"changed after the pool has been created.  The most important decision is "
"what types of vdevs into which to group the physical disks.  See the list of "
"<<zfs-term-vdev,vdev types>> for details about the possible options.  After "
"the pool has been created, most vdev types do not allow additional disks to "
"be added to the vdev.  The exceptions are mirrors, which allow additional "
"disks to be added to the vdev, and stripes, which can be upgraded to mirrors "
"by attaching an additional disk to the vdev.  Although additional vdevs can "
"be added to expand a pool, the layout of the pool cannot be changed after "
"pool creation.  Instead, the data must be backed up and the pool destroyed "
"and recreated."
